items.html: Here are the lab tests you can perform in your office. If a test isn't in this list, you'll need to send it to the lab services provider in your state. Please reference your Quick Reference Guide, which can be found under Plan Resources on our Providers page.
• Blood, occult, by peroxidase activity (e.g. guaiac), qualitative, feces, 1-3 simultaneous determinations, performed for other than colorectal neoplasm screening (82272)
• Blood, occult, by peroxidase activity (e.g. guaiac), qualitative; other sources (82271)
• Cell count, miscellaneous body fluids, except blood, with differential count (89051)
• Compete blood count (CBC), automated (HgB, HcT, RBW, WBC, and platelet count) and automated differential WBC count (85025)
• Crystal identification by light microscopy with or without polarizing lens analysis or body fluid (except urine) (89060)
• Culture, bacterial, screening only, for single organisms (87081)
• Culture, bacterial; any other source but urine, blood or stool, with isolation andpresumptive identification of isolates (87070)
• Gases, blood, any combination of pH, pCO2, pO2, CO2, HCO3 (including calculated O2 saturation) (82803)
• Helicobacter pylori, breath test analysis; drug administration (83014)
• Infections agent detection by immunoassay with direct optical observation; adenovirus (87809)
• Infectious agent antigen detection by enzyme immunoassay technique, qualitative or semi quantitative, multiple step method, Influenza A or B, each (87400)
• Infectious agent antigen detection by enzyme immunoassay technique, qualitative or semi quantitative, multiple step method; respiratory syncytial virus (87420)
• Infectious agent antigen detection by enzyme immunoassay technique, qualitative or semi quantitative, multiple step method; rotavirus (87425)
• Infectious agent antigen detection by enzyme immunoassay technique, Streptococcus, group A (87430)
• Infectious agent detection by immunoassay with direct optical observation; influenza (Rapid Flu) (87804)
• Infectious agent detection by immunoassay with direct optical observation; Streptococcus, group A (Rapid Strep) (87880)
• Infectious agent detection by nucleic acid (DNA or RNA); streptococus, group A, amplified probe technique (87651)
• Ova and parasites, direct smears, concentration and identification (87177)
• Tissue examination by KOH slide of samples from skin, hair, or nails for fungi or ectoparasite ova or mites (e.g. scabies) (87220)
• Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent, automated with microscopy (81001)
• Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent, automated without microscopy (81003)
• Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent, non-automated with microscopy (81000)
• Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent, non-automated without microscopy (81002)
• Urinalysis, qualitative or semi quantitative, except immunoassays (81005)
• Urine pregnancy test, by visual color comparison methods (81025)
• Wet mount for infection agents (e.g. saline, India ink, KOH preps) (87210)
• Blood count; automated differential WBC count blood smear, microscopic examination with manual differential WBC count (85007)
• Bone marrow; smear interpretation only, with or without differential cell count (85097)
Devoted Health Guides are here 8am to 8pm, 7 days a week.
Or call us at 1-800-DEVOTED (338–6833) TTY 711
